lisp_spec:
(defun find-sigma (lst)
  "Find the index of the first occurrence of 'SIGMA' in LST."
  (let ((index 0)) ; Initialize an index counter to zero
    (loop for element across lst                     ; Iterate through each element in the list
          do (setf index (+ index 1))                ; Increment the index by one at each iteration
          while (not (equal element 'sigma))        ; Continue until we find 'SIGMA' or reach the end of the list
          when (= element 'sigma)                   ; If 'SIGMA' is found, return its index
            return index)))                         ; Return the current index value
    nil))                                           ; If 'SIGMA' was not found in the list, return nil
